Dropping columns with more than 50% NA values and updating the numeric and categorical column lists¶

In [19]:
for col in data_to_cat.columns:
#     print("\n",col)
    x=data_to_cat.loc[:,col].isnull()
#     print("Percent NA values :",sum(x)*100/len(x))
    if(sum(x)*100/len(x)>=50):
        data_to_cat.drop(col,inplace=True,axis=1)

Summary of visualisations¶

  • The Loan Amount of the Charged-off people is greater than that of Fully-Paid.A loan amount of roughly 12000 and above is most is likely to default.
  • The debt to income ratio (dti) of defaulters is greater. The median dti is around 14-15
  • The annual income of the defaulters is less with median around 50000 per month
  • The Interest Rate of the defaulters is significantly higher with a median of about 0.17 while that that of the non-defaulters is below 0.125
  • People with more than 1 Inquery in last 6 months are likely to default.
  • Grades B,C,D have the most defaulters in count and give very less gain to the bank
  • 36 months term loans are likely to default more often than 60 months term loans
  • Emp Length of 10+ years and less than 1 year are likely to default . Emp-length of 2-5 years are also of some concern
  • People with House Ownership as Rent or Mortgage have high chances of defaulting.
  • People With Loan purpose as debt consolidation and "other" are likely to default
